Directional derivatives and scalar components

How is the derivative of a differentialble function f(x, y, z)
at a point P0 in the direction of a unit vector u related to the
scalar component of (∇f)P0 in the direction of u?

    if ∇f = ai + bj + ck

    U = ai + bj + ck

    u = U/|U| = a/sqrt(a² + b² + c²) i + b/sqrt(a² + b² + c²) j + c/sqrt(a² + b² + c²) k

    D = ∇f · u = a²/sqrt(a² + b² + c²) i + b²/sqrt(a² + b² + c²) j + c²/sqrt(a² + b² + c²) k
